        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A tropical infectious disease caused by the Gram-negative bacterium <i>Burkholderia pseudomallei</i> which is present in soil and water in tropical countries. Melioidosis can present itself in many ways including pneumonia sepsis and abscess formation."
        },
